concept.title: DONUT Command
concept.shortdesc: Creates a closed polyline in the shape of a donut.

conbody.p: Create a closed polyline in the shape of a donut from a combination of options including the inside diameter, outside diameter, center and width.

section.title: Methods to create a donut
section.p: There are four methods to begin creating a donut:

dlentry.dd: Begin creating a donut by specifying its inside diameter then:
Specify the outside diameter of the donut.
Specify the center of the donut to place it in the drawing. You can continue placing donuts of the same size until you press Enter to end the command.
Begin creating a donut by specifying its width then:
Specify a point on the diameter.

dd.p: Specify the second point on the diameter.

dlentry.dd: Begin creating a donut by specifying its width then:
Specify a point on the circumference of an imaginary circle that runs through the center of its width.
Specify the second point on the circumference of the imaginary circle.
Specify the third point on the circumference of the imaginary circle.
Begin creating a donut by selecting a tangent point on the first entity then:

dlentry.dt: Specify point on object for second tangent on donut
dlentry.dd: Select a tangent point on the second entity.
Specify the width of the donut.
Specify a valid diameter for the donut. If you specify a diameter that is not possible with the selected tangents, you are prompted to specify the tangents and diameter again.
